On DB Server, postgress is already installed

1. CREATE A USER "DEMOUSER" WITH passwordas "demopassword"
2. CREATE A DB NAMED "DEMODB" AND GRANT ALL PERLMISSIONS TO THE USER

SOLUTION:
Login to DBServer
switch to postgress - sudo -i -u postgres
  psql
user creation: CREATE USER "demouser" with PASSWORD 'demopassword';
db creation: CREATE DATABASE "DEMODB";
ALL PERMISSION:
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON demodb TO demouser ;
to check
  databse : \l
  database user : \du
